\subsection{Method \code{connect()}}{
Open the Connection

Wires the socket callbacks and starts connecting, then returns immediately
(non-blocking) — handlers only fire once something pumps \code{later}. Idempotent:
a no-op if already connecting or open. Use \verb{$run()} to drive the loop
yourself, or call \verb{$connect()} when the client lives inside a host that
already runs a \code{later} loop.
