\subsection{Method \code{run()}}{
Run the Event Loop (keep the process alive)

Connects if needed, then blocks and pumps R's \code{later} event loop so handlers
keep firing. Runs until \verb{$close()} is called or reconnects are exhausted.
Teardown is clean and guaranteed — a normal close, an interrupt (Ctrl-C), or
an error all close the socket and cancel timers via \code{on.exit()}. An interrupt
returns quietly; any other error still propagates after cleanup.
